            . I live in <placeName id="t18150913-128-crimeloc740">Hungerford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18150913-128-crimeloc740" type="placeName" value="Hungerford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18150913-128-crimeloc740" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18150913-128-off738 t18150913-128-crimeloc740"></join>. The prisoner came to my house for a night's lodging; I let him have one, for which he was to pay a shilling; and he went to bed at about half past ten. The things named in the indictment were let to him with the lodging; he paid me for his bed the night before. He came down at six o'clock in the morning, had a glass of gin, and then went out; and I missed the things in about five minutes afterwards.</p>
               <p>JOHN BRADLEY. I belong to St. Martin's watchhouse, and on searching the prisoner, found the counterpane wrapt round his body, and a sheet round each thigh. Here are the things.</p>
